Fairy\n|evo1={{bag|Rare Candy}}<br>{{color2|000|Level|Level 19}}\n|no2=670\n|name2=Floette\n|type1-2=Fairy\n|evo2={{bag|Shiny Stone}}<br>{{color2|000|Shiny Stone}}\n|no3=671\n|name3=Florges\n|type1-3=Fairy\n}}\n\n===Sprites===\n{{Spritebox/Header|type=fairy}}\n{{Spritebox/NA|gen=VI}}\n{{Spritebox/6/5Forms|ndex=671|form1=Y|form2=O|form3=B|form4=W}}\n{{Spritebox/7/5Forms|ndex=671|form1=Y|form2=O|form3=B|form4=W}}\n{{Spritebox/Footer|671|Florges}}\n\n==Trivia==\n* Florges has the highest base {{stat|Special Defense}} stat of all {{type|Fairy}} Pokémon.\n* Florges is the only Pokémon with a base stat total of 552.\n\n===Origin===\nFlorges appears to be based on {{wp|fairy|fairies}} and {{wp|nymphs}}, in particular {{wp|Anthousai}} due to its floral "hair". Its ornate, flowery "hair" may also be a reference to the 18th century {{wp|pouf}} hairstyle, which was notable in that the style would commonly use decorative items within the hair itself to convey mood and uniqueness. Its body structure resembles that of the {{wp|hyacinth}} flower, which has large sturdy leaves projecting from the base of the stalk. Its design may also draw inspiration from {{wp|mermaids}}.\n\n====Name origin====\nFlorges may be a combination of \'\'flora\'\' and \'\'gorgeous\'\'.\n\n==In other languages==\n{{Other languages|type=fairy|type2=fairy\n|ja=フラージェス \'\'Florges\'\'|jameaning=From \'\'flower\'\' and \'\'gorgeous\'\'\n|fr=Florges|frmeaning=Same as English name\n|es=Florges|esmeaning=Same as English name\n|de=Florges|demeaning=Same as English name\n|it=Florges|itmeaning=Same as English name\n|ko=플라제스 \'\'Peulrajeseu\'\'|komeaning=Transliteration of its Japanese name\n|zh_yue=花潔夫人 \'\'Fāgitfùhyàhn\'\'|zh_yuemeaning=From {{tt|花 \'\'fā\'\'|flower}}, {{tt|潔 \'\'git\'\'|clean}}, and {{tt|夫人 \'\'fùhyàhn\'\'|madam}}\n|zh_cmn=花潔夫人 / 花洁夫人 \'\'Huājiéfūrén\'\'|zh_cmnmeaning=From {{tt|花 \'\'huā\'\'|flower}}, {{tt|潔 / 洁 \'\'jié\'\'|clean}}, and {{tt|夫人 \'\'fūrén\'\'|madam}}\n|hi=फ्लोरगेस \'\'Florges\'\'|h